Date: Fri, 10 Oct 2014
Source: The News.com [Edited]
http://www.thenews.com.pk/Todays-News-4-277346-Naegleria-claims-another-life;two-more


_Naegleria fowleri_ claims life of woman in Karachi
------------------------------
The amoeba, _Naegleria fowleri_, which causes an encephalitis claimed a woman's life on Thursday [9 Oct 2014] as a man affected by the illness continued to fight for his life at a private hospital, said health officials.

The patient, [a 25 year old female], was brought to the Aga Khan University Hospital a day earlier [8 Oct 2014] with high fever and was later diagnosed with Naegleria. She passed away while being treated at the hospital.

Karachi Health Director Dr Zafar Aijaz said the deceased was a resident of Taiser Town Karachi. Another patient, [a 45 year old male], also tested positive for the illness and was currently admitted for treatment in Liaquat National Hospital. The doctors said [he] was unconscious and had been placed on a ventilator.

