[Pakistan is reporting more cases at present than any other country. It is important that the diagnosis rests on solid ground with Naegleria fowleri DNA being demonstrated in cerebrospinal fluid or brain biopsies. Concerning possible routes of transmission it is discussed in the ProMED moderator's comment in prior ProMED-mail post Amebic meningoencephalitis, primary - Pakistan (03): 20140903.2746573. - Mod.EP]
